http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Seminar-to-promote-tourism-sedctor-in-Udupi-on-January-15/article13975922.ece

The Udupi Chamber of Commerce and Industry will be organising a seminar on “Udupi tourism for everyone” here on January 15. Addressing presspersons here on Friday, K. Srikrishna Rao, president of the chamber, said there was a lot of tourism potential in Udupi. Udupi not only houses the famous Sri Krishna Mutt/Temple but also has a fine beach at Malpe.The seminar would focus on the ways and means of developing tourism here.The topics to be discussed at the seminar would include: Udupi tourism – What next?; Karnataka Government Tourism Plan 2016-20; Udupi tourism – opportunities for everyone; and Tourism and entrepreneurship.